{
  "texts": [
    "In general, it suggests that recent studies have centered on addressing the gap between research and practical application in the field of AI ethics.",
    "This also involves the development of various tools and methods aimed at improving the ethical implementation of AI.",
    "Overall, existing studies seem to primarily focus on either analysing the plethora of ethical AI principles, filling the gap between research and practice, or discussing tool-kits and methods.",
    "However, compared to the number of papers on AI ethics describing ethical guidelines and principles, and tools and methods, there is a relative lack of studies that focus on the views and experiences of AI practitioners on AI ethics (Vakkuri et al. 2020b).",
    "Furthermore, the literature also underscores the necessity for review studies that evaluate and synthesise the existing primary research on AI practitioners' views and experiences of AI ethics (Khan et al. 2022; Leikas et al. 2019)."
  ]
}